=begin pod
=head2 remove

Remove a tag from the table.

If a L<Gnome::Gtk4::TextBuffer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/TextBuffer> has C<$table> as its tag table, the tag is
removed from the buffer. The table’s reference to the tag is
removed, so the tag will end up destroyed if you don’t have
a reference to it.

=begin code
method remove ( N-Object() $tag )
=end code

=item $tag; a L<Gnome::Gtk4::TextTag|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/TextTag>.

